Bob: Is your code compiling fine? These errors show up when you try to 
run/debug it, right?

> Is your code compiling fine? These errors show up when you try to run/debug
it, right?

Right.

This looks odd to me (I'm not sure how the original dump was generated - was it 
a "copy" on the call stack?).

The debugger keeps a cache of "locations" to compilation errors, which it 
creates on (plug-in) startup, and updates incrementally as builds occurr. When 
a "java.lang.Exception" is thrown, we look to see if there are any known 
compilation errors at the current exeucution location, and report as such.

It looks like this cache is out of date with the workspace. Restarting the 
workspace should resolve the problem, as we re-build this cache. Let me know if 
re-starting the workspace solves the immediate problem.

Exiting and restarting Eclipse solves the immediate problem. I can debug again.

I was sure I'd tried this yesterday, but it did work today, so maybe not. I will
try to be more conscious of what precedes the error state, if I see it again.

I'm going to mark this as works for me. Clearly there is bug somewhere - but 
it's not clear how this happenned. If it happens again please re-open.
